.TH "TEMPORAL.ZONEDDATETIME.WITHCALENDAR" "3JS" "December 8, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
Temporal.ZonedDateTime.withCalendar \-
Temporal.ZonedDateTime.prototype.withCalendar()
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]withCalendar()\f[B]\f[R] method of
\f[CR]Temporal.ZonedDateTime\f[R] instances returns a new
\f[CR]Temporal.ZonedDateTime\f[R] object representing this date\-time
interpreted in the new calendar system.
Because all \f[CR]Temporal\f[R] objects are designed to be immutable,
this method essentially functions as the setter for the date\-time\(cqs
\f[CR]calendarId\f[R] property.
.PP
To replace the date\-time component properties, use the
\f[CR]with()\f[R] method.
To replace its time zone, use the \f[CR]withTimeZone()\f[R] method.
.SH SYNTAX
.IP
.EX
withCalendar(calendar)
.EE
.SS Parameters
.TP
\f[B]calendar\f[R]
A string that corresponds to the \f[CR]calendarId\f[R] property.
See \f[CR]Intl.supportedValuesOf()\f[R] for a list of commonly supported
calendar types.
.SS Return value
A new \f[CR]Temporal.ZonedDateTime\f[R] object, representing the
date\-time specified by the original \f[CR]ZonedDateTime\f[R],
interpreted in the new calendar system.
.SS Exceptions
.TP
\f[B]TypeError\f[R]
Thrown if \f[CR]calendar\f[R] is not a string.
.TP
\f[B]RangeError\f[R]
Thrown if \f[CR]calendar\f[R] is not a valid calendar identifier.
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Using withCalendar()
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] zdt = Temporal.ZonedDateTime.from(
  \(dq2021\-07\-01T12:34:56[America/New_York]\(dq,
);
\f[B]const\f[R] newZDT = zdt.withCalendar(\(dqislamic\-umalqura\(dq);
console.log(newZDT.toLocaleString(\(dqen\-US\(dq, { calendar: \(dqislamic\-umalqura\(dq }));
\f[I]// 11/21/1442 AH, 12:34:56 PM EDT\f[R]
.EE
